(1357, 348, 'artist_content', 'What simply started as a search for the perfect cake is what truly sparked an idea. With a gigantic sweet tooth, it was always unsatisfying to eat cakes that were either too sweet, too dry, or too bland. A good baker can always balance the elements of a perfect creation. In addition, having family members with diabetes has helped me come up with a perfect recipe that they too can savour. It is important for me to create treats that everyone can enjoy without feeling guilty. After being told for years to turn my talent into a business, Sweet Fix Bakery was born.\r\n\r\nI haven’t taken any classes, or had any formal pastry training. I have studied at McMaster University and obtained my Bachelor of Sciences. I have been a chemist for 7 years, but decided to turn my passion and hobby into an opportunity. Sweet Fix Bakery is as simple as its name. Baked goodies just to get over that craving for sweets without over indulging; unless of course you want to...\r\n\r\nCouture cakes without boutique prices. Made just for you with the freshest of ingredients.\r\n\r\nLooking forward to hearing from you!'),
